==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Houndfish
<hw>Hound"fish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any small shark of the genus <gen>Galeus</gen> or
<gen>Mustelus</gen>, of which there are several species, as the smooth
houndfish (<spn>Galeus canis</spn>), of Europe and America; -- called
also <altname>houndshark</altname>, and
<altname>dogfish</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The European nursehound, or small-spotted dogfish, is
<spn>Scyllium canicula</spn>; the rough houndfish, or large-spotted
dogfish, is <spn>Scyllium catulus</spn>. The name has also sometimes
been applied to the bluefish (<spn>Pomatomus saltatrix</spn>), and to
the silver gar.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hounding</ent>⟦br⟧
